WEBVTT

00:11:57.775 --> 00:12:02.242
with someone they have been taught
to associate with danger.

00:12:02.744 --> 00:12:05.964
My son senses their discomfort,

00:12:05.988 --> 00:12:09.145
and he smiles to put them at ease,

00:12:09.169 --> 00:12:10.938
to calm their fears.

00:12:11.351 --> 00:12:13.296
When he speaks,

00:12:13.320 --> 00:12:15.003
their bodies relax.

00:12:15.442 --> 00:12:17.345
They breathe easier.

00:12:17.369 --> 00:12:19.900
They take pleasure in his cadence,

00:12:19.924 --> 00:12:22.241
his diction, his word choice.

00:12:22.986 --> 00:12:24.829
He sounds like one of them.

00:12:24.853 --> 00:12:29.583
I used to think that my son
was a natural extrovert like his father.

00:12:29.607 --> 00:12:33.157
But I realized at that moment,
in that conversation,